The paper discusses the effects of online social networking on offline interactions and collective well-being, which falls under the category of social interactions. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses an evolutionary game framework to model socialization strategies, which could fall under cs.CY (Computational Biology and Bioinformatics) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses the implications for collective well-being, which could fall under cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) or cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
